ce:section.ce:para:
Hybrid particles with N-CDs and biopolymers, CGCDs were prepared and utilized as an adsorbent for HMI. N-CDs were characterized carefully before the preparation of CGCDs. The surface morphologies of N-CDs were examined using FE-SEM (Fig. 1
                     ). Fig. 1a displays the smooth surface of N-CDs with a wrinkled structure. Further, elemental mapping (Fig. 1b–d) divulges the even distribution of C, O, and N elements on the N-CDs surface. In addition, the EDX spectra of N-CDs (Fig. 1e) demonstrate the presence of C, O, and N elements. The morphology was further characterized by TEM/HR-TEM (Fig. 2
                     ). TEM images confirm the spherical shape of N-CDs, the inset of Fig. 2a (HR-TEM image) discloses the lattice fringes of N-CDs. The interlayer distance was calculated as ~0.21 nm, which matches well with the (100) plane of graphene/graphite (Atchudan et al., 2016; You et al., 2016; Wu et al., 2017). The average particle size was calculated as 4.0 nm, and the corresponding size distribution graph is depicted in Fig. 2b.
